# Static-analysis policy for the project-owned C core (modules/). Bug-finding
# families only; style is clang-format's job. Enforced by the clang-tidy CI
# gate over the host-compilable file set (tests/host/sources.sh).
#
# Disabled checks:
#  - easily-swappable-parameters: wire/crypto APIs take adjacent byte-buffer
#    pointers and lengths by nature; the check flags nearly every prototype.
#  - reserved-identifier (+ its cert aliases dcl37-c/dcl51-cpp): the CCC shim's
#    __wrap_/__real_ symbols are the linker's --wrap contract and IS_ENABLED's
#    _XXXX1 is the Zephyr token-paste idiom; those names are required, not chosen.
#  - insecureAPI.DeprecatedOrUnsafeBufferHandling: flags every fixed-length
#    memcpy/memset and prescribes Annex K memcpy_s, which none of this code's
#    libcs (glibc, Darwin, Zephyr minimal) implement. Fires target-dependently
#    (Linux yes, Darwin no), so keep it explicit or CI and local runs disagree.
Checks: >
  -*,
  bugprone-*,
  cert-*,
  clang-analyzer-*,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters,
  -bugprone-reserved-identifier,
  -cert-dcl37-c,
  -cert-dcl51-cpp,
  -clang-analyzer-security.insecureAPI.DeprecatedOrUnsafeBufferHandling
WarningsAsErrors: "*"
